The paper proposes the use of intelligent conversation generators to create data-driven conversation interfaces from open data and deliver personalized analytical insights to users based on their contextual needs. This involves the integration of AI, human-centric design, natural language processing, and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.HC (human-computer interaction), cs.CL (computational linguistics), cs.DB (databases), and cs.IR (information retrieval).
